input_args.text: 'Ryan McMaken https://www.lewrockwell.com/lrc-blog/trade-agreements-political-independence-false-choice/ \nThe rejection of the Comprehensive Economic and Trade Agreement (CETA) by Beligium is a bittersweet affair. But, it’s always worth remembering that intergovernmental trade agreements are not equivalent to free trade, and in fact are purported to bring about a reduction in the ease of trade and an increase in costs favorable to some particularly well-connected interest groups to the detriment of consumers. Carmen Elena Dorobăț explains . 10:23 am on October 28, 2016'
